The paper discusses the complexity of recognizing edges in computation paths and clusters, which is a central topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also deals with the definition and robustness of cluster classes, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). Finally, the paper explores closure properties of cluster classes, which is related to the study of graph theory (cs.GT).
